2
00:02:00.210 --> 00:02:01.460
Keep breathing.

3
00:02:07.590 --> 00:02:08.970
And push.

4
00:02:17.140 --> 00:02:18.180
And again.

5
00:02:19.730 --> 00:02:21.270
I can't...

6
00:02:22.690 --> 00:02:23.730
Push.

7
00:02:27.650 --> 00:02:28.690
The head

8
00:02:42.460 --> 00:02:45.040
A boy. Princess. Praise the Mother

9
00:02:59.770 --> 00:03:02.350
Healthy? Kicking like a goat. Princess.

10
00:03:17.620 --> 00:03:18.660
Princess.

11
00:03:20.240 --> 00:03:24.580
The Queen has requested that the child be brought to her... immediately.

12
00:03:27.920 --> 00:03:28.960
Why?

13
00:03:39.510 --> 00:03:40.680
I'll take him myself.

14
00:03:40.770 --> 00:03:44.020
You should remain abed. Princess... Yes. I should  Help me dress.

15
00:04:01.740 --> 00:04:02.910
Princess...

16
00:04:04.580 --> 00:04:05.620
your dress?

17
00:04:40.490 --> 00:04:42.370
- Princess? - It's coming.

18
00:04:42.450 --> 00:04:43.490
The afterbirth.

19
00:04:53.750 --> 00:04:55.970
A boy. I've just heard.

20
00:04:56.050 --> 00:04:57.470
- Yes. - Well done.

21
00:04:59.140 --> 00:05:02.050
- Where are you going? - She wants to see him.

22
00:05:02.140 --> 00:05:03.180
Now?

23
00:05:04.470 --> 00:05:05.680
I'm coming with you.

24
00:05:05.770 --> 00:05:07.730
- I should hope so. - Let me take him.

25
00:05:07.810 --> 00:05:09.560
No. she'll get no such satisfaction from me.

26
00:05:09.650 --> 00:05:11.480
Just take my arm. at the least.

27
00:05:16.490 --> 00:05:17.820
Was it terribly painful?

28
00:05:20.070 --> 00:05:21.240
Oh. gods.

29
00:05:26.160 --> 00:05:28.000
I took a lance through the shoulder once.

30
00:05:29.370 --> 00:05:30.920
My deepest sympathies.

31
00:05:31.630 --> 00:05:33.210
- The Princess... - The Princess...

32
00:05:33.290 --> 00:05:35.840
I am glad I am not a woman.

33
00:05:35.920 --> 00:05:37.420
My Princess... My lord...

34
00:05:43.430 --> 00:05:44.470
What is it?

35
00:05:45.640 --> 00:05:46.890
What is it? What is it?

36
00:05:47.930 --> 00:05:48.980
Fuck.

37
00:05:49.560 --> 00:05:51.650
Walk. Walk

38
00:05:57.190 --> 00:05:58.820
What could she possibly want?

39
00:06:01.070 --> 00:06:02.490
I thought we were past this.

40
00:06:07.330 --> 00:06:08.950
Princess. Ser Laenor. it is a privilege

41
00:06:09.040 --> 00:06:12.330
to be amongst the first to congratulate you.

42
00:06:12.420 --> 00:06:13.670
Thank you. Lord Caswell.

43
00:06:14.210 --> 00:06:17.130
If I may be of any service.

44
00:06:17.210 --> 00:06:19.170
The day may yet come. my lord.

45
00:06:26.970 --> 00:06:31.020
We are turning back. all right? She can come to us. all right?

46
00:06:31.100 --> 00:06:34.400
No. Not unless you wish to carry me down those fucking stairs.

47
00:06:52.290 --> 00:06:53.420
This is absurd.

48
00:07:10.850 --> 00:07:11.890
Princess.

49
00:07:29.830 --> 00:07:30.870
Rhaenyra.

50
00:07:31.620 --> 00:07:33.790
You should be resting after your labors.

51
00:07:35.370 --> 00:07:38.090
I have no doubt that you would prefer that. Your Grace.

52
00:07:38.170 --> 00:07:39.210
You must sit.

53
00:07:39.840 --> 00:07:41.960
Talya. fetch a cushion for the Princess.

54
00:07:42.050 --> 00:07:44.180
- There's no need. - Nonsense.

55
00:07:45.380 --> 00:07:46.430
We'll finish this later.

56
00:07:48.470 --> 00:07:49.510
Your Grace.

57
00:07:56.060 --> 00:07:58.150
What happy news this morning.

58
00:07:58.230 --> 00:07:59.480
Indeed. Your Grace.

59
00:08:00.570 --> 00:08:01.820
Where is he?

60
00:08:02.820 --> 00:08:05.780
Where is my grandson? There.

61
00:08:07.620 --> 00:08:09.280
There he is.

62
00:08:12.870 --> 00:08:14.500
A fine Prince.

63
00:08:15.290 --> 00:08:16.330
Sturdy.

64
00:08:16.830 --> 00:08:19.040
You will make a fearsome knight.

65
00:08:20.000 --> 00:08:22.880
Yes. you will. Does the babe have a name yet?

66
00:08:23.920 --> 00:08:25.420
- We haven't spoken... - Joffrey.

67
00:08:26.630 --> 00:08:28.010
He'll be called Joffrey.

68
00:08:28.510 --> 00:08:30.350
That's an unusual name for a Velaryon.

69
00:08:33.060 --> 00:08:35.310
I do believe he has his father's nose.

70
00:08:37.100 --> 00:08:38.400
Don't you?

71
00:08:44.570 --> 00:08:47.820
If you don't mind. Your Grace your daughter has exerted herself heroically

72
00:08:47.910 --> 00:08:50.280
and should rest. Of course.

73
00:08:52.410 --> 00:08:53.450
There.

74
00:09:02.500 --> 00:09:03.920
Well done. my girl.

75
00:09:06.420 --> 00:09:08.300
I do hope the labor was easy.

76
00:09:09.550 --> 00:09:12.050
I think I called the midwife a cunt.

77
00:09:20.190 --> 00:09:22.190
Do keep trying. Ser Laenor.

78
00:09:23.400 --> 00:09:25.610
Soon or late. you may get one who looks like you.

79
00:09:40.250 --> 00:09:43.920
You don't think to consult me before you name my child?

80
00:09:44.420 --> 00:09:46.210
He's our child. is he not?

81
00:09:48.130 --> 00:09:49.760
Only one of us is bleeding.

82
00:09:50.380 --> 00:09:53.220
I deserve some say in the affairs of my own family.

83
00:09:54.220 --> 00:09:56.560
You haven't seemed so interested in our affairs of late.

84
00:10:09.450 --> 00:10:12.530
And he sees a big. scary dragon

85
00:10:17.830 --> 00:10:18.870
Mother.

86
00:10:19.620 --> 00:10:20.750
Look.

87
00:10:26.000 --> 00:10:27.760
We chose an egg for the baby.

88
00:10:29.590 --> 00:10:31.930
That looks like the perfect one.

89
00:10:32.010 --> 00:10:34.010
- I let Luke choose. - Thank you. Jace.

90
00:10:34.930 --> 00:10:37.390
Not every day an egg leaves the Dragonpit. Princess.

91
00:10:37.470 --> 00:10:40.140
I thought it best to escort the lads.

92
00:10:42.100 --> 00:10:43.690
Laenor and I thank you. Commander.

93
00:10:45.610 --> 00:10:47.440
Another boy. I heard.

94
00:10:52.450 --> 00:10:54.910
What a fine knight you are going to make. eh?

95
00:10:55.490 --> 00:10:56.530
Might I?

96
00:10:58.370 --> 00:11:01.160
Ser Harwin wishes to be introduced to Joffrey.

97
00:11:03.460 --> 00:11:04.500
Of course.

98
00:11:06.420 --> 00:11:07.590
Joffrey. is it?

99
00:11:15.930 --> 00:11:18.220
Father. please. may I hold Joffrey?

100
00:11:18.310 --> 00:11:22.850
No... - Back to the Dragonpit for you two.

101
00:11:22.940 --> 00:11:25.480
- Come on  Before they send out a search party.

102
00:11:37.240 --> 00:11:39.740
You're asleep in front of the Commander of the City Watch.

103
00:11:42.000 --> 00:11:43.330
Terrible lack of respect.

104
00:11:43.870 --> 00:11:46.830
A certain insolence runs in the family. I'm afraid.

105
00:12:39.140 --> 00:12:40.760
Call Vermax to heel. Prince Jacaerys.

106
00:13:17.130 --> 00:13:18.470
Vermax

107
00:13:19.010 --> 00:13:20.050
Vermax

108
00:13:29.190 --> 00:13:32.440
You must hold mastery over your dragon. my young princes.

109
00:13:34.270 --> 00:13:36.360
As Prince Aegon has with Sunfyre.

110
00:13:43.580 --> 00:13:47.200
Once they're fully bound to you they will refuse to take instruction from any other.

111
00:13:51.210 --> 00:13:52.250
Can I say it?

112
00:14:00.180 --> 00:14:01.640
Dracarys. Vermax

113
00:14:24.580 --> 00:14:26.740
Aemond. we have a surprise for you.

114
00:14:28.040 --> 00:14:30.210
- What is it? - Something very special.

115
00:14:32.210 --> 00:14:34.080
You're the only one of us without a dragon.

116
00:14:34.250 --> 00:14:37.250
Indeed. And we felt badly about it

117
00:14:38.050 --> 00:14:41.800
so we found one for you. A dragon?

118
00:14:42.680 --> 00:14:45.300
How? The gods provide.

119
00:14:54.020 --> 00:14:56.650
Behold... The Pink Dread

120
00:14:59.650 --> 00:15:02.570
Be sure to mount her carefully. First flight's always rough.

121
00:16:39.670 --> 00:16:41.090
This one has 60 rings...

122
00:16:42.500 --> 00:16:43.920
and two pairs of legs on each.

123
00:16:45.050 --> 00:16:46.470
That's 240.

124
00:16:47.840 --> 00:16:48.930
Yes. it is.

125
00:16:51.720 --> 00:16:52.760
It has eyes

126
00:16:54.060 --> 00:16:55.100
though...

127
00:16:55.850 --> 00:16:57.310
I don't believe it can see.

128
00:16:58.810 --> 00:17:00.770
And why is that so. do you think?

129
00:17:03.030 --> 00:17:04.610
It is beyond our understanding.

130
00:17:07.150 --> 00:17:09.780
I suppose you're right. Some things just are.

131
00:17:13.910 --> 00:17:14.950
Your Grace.

132
00:17:16.870 --> 00:17:20.540
Aemond. - What have you done? - He did it again.

133
00:17:20.630 --> 00:17:23.300
After how many times you've been warned must I have you confined to your chambers?

134
00:17:23.380 --> 00:17:25.420
- They made me do it  - As if you needed encouragement.

135
00:17:25.510 --> 00:17:28.760
Your obsession with those beasts goes beyond understanding. They gave me a pig

136
00:17:29.510 --> 00:17:32.180
A what? They said they found a dragon for me.

137
00:17:32.260 --> 00:17:35.390
The last ring has no legs at all. But it was a pig.

138
00:17:36.520 --> 00:17:38.560
You will have a dragon one day.

139
00:17:39.350 --> 00:17:41.690
- He'll have to close an eye. - I know it.

140
00:17:43.570 --> 00:17:44.690
They all laughed.

141
00:17:48.860 --> 00:17:50.740
They made wings for it. apparently.

142
00:17:50.820 --> 00:17:51.870
and a tail.

143
00:17:51.950 --> 00:17:54.790
The lad shouldn't have been so credulous. He's a child.

144
00:17:54.870 --> 00:17:58.040
He thought they'd happened upon some wild unnamed dragon

145
00:17:58.120 --> 00:17:59.500
and lured it to the Dragonpit?

146
00:17:59.580 --> 00:18:02.920
Your grandsons are a menace. They're more children than he is.

147
00:18:03.000 --> 00:18:05.750
They're savages. And it's not surprising.

148
00:18:08.130 --> 00:18:11.050
Are you sure it wasn't our Aegon who put them up to it?

149
00:18:14.970 --> 00:18:17.020
It's a wonder to me their eggs ever hatched.

150
00:18:18.520 --> 00:18:20.520
- And why is that? - You know why.

151
00:18:20.600 --> 00:18:22.270
- I'm afraid I don't. - Don't...

152
00:18:24.060 --> 00:18:25.190
Viserys.

153
00:18:27.820 --> 00:18:29.610
We shall continue this afternoon. Eddard.

154
00:18:38.700 --> 00:18:41.120
I have raised this matter before

155
00:18:41.210 --> 00:18:43.750
and you forbade me to speak of it so I held my tongue.

156
00:18:45.710 --> 00:18:48.000
To have one child like that is a mistake.

157
00:18:48.090 --> 00:18:50.840
To have three is an insult

158
00:18:50.920 --> 00:18:52.220
to the throne. to you. to House Velaryon

159
00:18:52.930 --> 00:18:55.850
and the match you battled so hard to make for her.

160
00:18:55.930 --> 00:18:58.470
Not to mention decency itself.

161
00:18:59.720 --> 00:19:01.600
I had a black mare once.

162
00:19:02.520 --> 00:19:04.270
Black like a raven.

163
00:19:04.440 --> 00:19:06.360
One day. she escaped her pasture

164
00:19:07.110 --> 00:19:09.730
and the neighboring stallion sired a foal on her.

165
00:19:12.110 --> 00:19:15.280
The stallion was as silver as the moon on a winter's night

166
00:19:16.320 --> 00:19:19.950
and the foal. when it was born. chestnut.

167
00:19:21.910 --> 00:19:25.750
Just the most unremarkable brown horse you ever saw.

168
00:19:27.840 --> 00:19:30.130
Nature is a thing of mysterious works.

169
00:19:36.720 --> 00:19:38.010
How do you know?

170
00:19:39.970 --> 00:19:43.560
The silver stallion. How do you know it was him?

171
00:19:45.480 --> 00:19:47.270
Did you witness the act itself?

172
00:19:51.490 --> 00:19:55.950
The consequences of an allegation like the one you toy at

173
00:19:57.030 --> 00:19:58.120
would be dire.

174
00:20:06.750 --> 00:20:08.500
Do not speak of this again.

175
00:20:19.350 --> 00:20:21.600
Have I lost my sanity. Ser Criston?

176
00:20:21.680 --> 00:20:24.020
Do my senses lead me astray or is everyone else asleep.

177
00:20:24.100 --> 00:20:27.560
dreaming the same woolly dream? Sometimes seems so. Your Grace.

178
00:20:30.440 --> 00:20:32.860
She flaunts the privilege of her inheritance without shame.

179
00:20:32.940 --> 00:20:36.070
She expects everyone in the Red Keep to deny the truth our eyes can all plainly see.

180
00:20:36.150 --> 00:20:37.570
- And the King. her father... - He knows.

181
00:20:37.660 --> 00:20:40.370
Of course he knows. Or did once but has convinced himself otherwise.

182
00:20:40.450 --> 00:20:42.290
He'll do naught but make excuses for her.

183
00:20:43.250 --> 00:20:46.830
The Princess Rhaenyra is brazen and relentless.

184
00:20:46.920 --> 00:20:50.000
A spider who stings and sucks her prey dry.

185
00:20:51.090 --> 00:20:52.380
A spoiled cunt.

186
00:20:58.430 --> 00:21:00.600
That was beneath me. Your Grace. I apologize.

187
00:21:04.180 --> 00:21:09.400
I have to believe that in the end. honor and decency will prevail.

188
00:21:10.810 --> 00:21:13.690
We need to hew to that and to each other.

189
00:21:32.920 --> 00:21:35.130
Whose idea was it?

190
00:21:39.510 --> 00:21:42.050
The pig. Was it your plot?

191
00:21:42.720 --> 00:21:43.810
No.

192
00:21:44.470 --> 00:21:45.680
It was Jace

193
00:21:46.390 --> 00:21:47.430
and...

194
00:21:49.140 --> 00:21:52.270
It was the two of them. I couldn't be sure.

195
00:21:52.360 --> 00:21:54.570
Aemond is your brother. - Well. he's a twat.

196
00:21:54.650 --> 00:21:58.450
- We are family. You may cuff him about as you wish at home

197
00:21:58.530 --> 00:22:01.700
but in the world. we must defend our own.

198
00:22:01.780 --> 00:22:02.870
It was funny.

199
00:22:02.950 --> 00:22:05.700
Do you think Rhaenyra's sons will be your playthings forever?

200
00:22:07.290 --> 00:22:08.540
As things stand...

201
00:22:09.500 --> 00:22:13.210
Rhaenyra will ascend the throne and Jacaerys Targaryen will be her heir.

202
00:22:13.840 --> 00:22:14.880
So?

203
00:22:15.500 --> 00:22:18.550
You are nearly a man grown. How is it that you can be so shortsighted?

204
00:22:21.220 --> 00:22:22.970
If Rhaenyra comes into power...

205
00:22:23.970 --> 00:22:26.390
your very life could be forfeit.

206
00:22:27.430 --> 00:22:28.560
Aemond's as well.

207
00:22:30.190 --> 00:22:32.900
She could move to cut off any challenge to her succession.

208
00:22:33.730 --> 00:22:35.520
- Then I won't challenge... - You are the challenge

209
00:22:35.610 --> 00:22:39.610
You are the challenge. Aegon  Simply by living and breathing

210
00:22:44.160 --> 00:22:46.330
You are the King's firstborn son

211
00:22:47.120 --> 00:22:50.080
and what they know. what everyone in the realm knows

212
00:22:50.160 --> 00:22:51.960
in their blood and in their bones...

213
00:22:53.290 --> 00:22:55.920
is that one day. you will be our King.

214
00:23:04.760 --> 00:23:06.220
Get dressed.

215
00:24:31.510 --> 00:24:33.850
The lamb hearts are excellent.

216
00:24:33.930 --> 00:24:36.640
We are fortunate in our cook. Your Excellence.

217
00:24:36.730 --> 00:24:38.060
There's a plum cake yet to be served

218
00:24:38.150 --> 00:24:40.110
which will have us fighting over the crumbs.

219
00:24:40.190 --> 00:24:42.530
Then before we come to blows...

220
00:24:43.740 --> 00:24:47.610
a toast to Aegon the Conqueror. your exalted forebear

221
00:24:47.700 --> 00:24:51.280
who joined our cause against Volantis in the Century of Blood.

222
00:24:51.660 --> 00:24:55.000
On the great dragon Balerion. he flew to our aid in Lys

223
00:24:55.080 --> 00:24:58.420
and burned a fleet of enemy ships. thus turning the tide.

224
00:25:00.750 --> 00:25:01.840
- Aegon the Conqueror.

225
00:25:01.920 --> 00:25:03.210
- To Aegon.

226
00:25:06.590 --> 00:25:08.300
This brings me to some business.

227
00:25:09.260 --> 00:25:10.850
A proposal I wish to make

228
00:25:11.680 --> 00:25:14.350
in the spirit of honoring our storied alliance.

229
00:25:14.430 --> 00:25:16.980
If your aim is to marry one of our daughters. Your Excellence

230
00:25:17.060 --> 00:25:19.100
you might have said so and spared us the history lesson.

231
00:25:19.520 --> 00:25:20.610
What?

232
00:25:21.520 --> 00:25:24.690
I would not count myself so deserving. my Lady Laena.

233
00:25:27.280 --> 00:25:31.120
I wish to offer you a permanent residence here in Pentos.

234
00:25:31.780 --> 00:25:34.120
This manse I would gift to you. outright

235
00:25:34.200 --> 00:25:38.410
along with its farms and lands. the vineyard and the wood.

236
00:25:38.500 --> 00:25:42.750
The tenants would pay their tributes annually to their new Targaryen lord.

237
00:25:42.840 --> 00:25:45.420
You would have your freedom of the city and the harbor

238
00:25:45.510 --> 00:25:47.760
as befits your royal station.

239
00:25:51.340 --> 00:25:52.720
Continue.

240
00:25:52.890 --> 00:25:56.140
Lys and its allies rise again.

241
00:25:56.220 --> 00:26:00.350
The Triarchy has made common cause with Qoren Martell of Dorne.

242
00:26:01.020 --> 00:26:03.820
At any moment. they may turn their sights north.

243
00:26:03.980 --> 00:26:05.820
Your family has dragons.

244
00:26:06.480 --> 00:26:10.030
Three now. mayhaps four in the future.

245
00:26:11.240 --> 00:26:15.120
My aim is to protect Pentos from the lustful eye of the Triarchy.

246
00:26:15.200 --> 00:26:18.580
Aid Pentos in this as Aegon once did

247
00:26:19.540 --> 00:26:23.250
and my gratitude will fill your cup and overflow it.

248
00:26:23.880 --> 00:26:28.510
Your Excellence. we are travelers. We've already extended our visit here.

249
00:26:33.220 --> 00:26:35.050
It's a most generous offer.

250
00:26:35.720 --> 00:26:37.310
And one we will certainly entertain.

251
00:27:08.300 --> 00:27:10.590
You are considering Prince Reggio's offer.

252
00:27:10.670 --> 00:27:11.760
We have a good life here.

253
00:27:12.970 --> 00:27:16.220
We're free to do as we please. welcomed and feted.

254
00:27:16.300 --> 00:27:18.640
- And eternally guests. - Precisely.

255
00:27:18.720 --> 00:27:21.730
We are without responsibility. The political scheming.

256
00:27:21.810 --> 00:27:26.110
The endless shifting of loyalties and succession is none of ours.

257
00:27:26.690 --> 00:27:29.480
- They are using us. - It's refreshing. isn't it?

258
00:27:31.360 --> 00:27:35.030
A simple transaction. We have dragons. they have gold.

259
00:27:40.700 --> 00:27:42.660
We are more than this. Daemon.

260
00:27:42.750 --> 00:27:45.750
We are not minstrels or mummers who play at the pleasure of an alien prince.

261
00:27:45.830 --> 00:27:48.040
We are the blood of Old Valyria.

262
00:27:49.300 --> 00:27:50.880
We don't belong here.

263
00:27:50.960 --> 00:27:53.090
Valyria is gone. We don't belong anywhere.

264
00:27:59.180 --> 00:28:02.560
I want my child to be born where I was born. on Driftmark

265
00:28:02.640 --> 00:28:05.100
in my lord father's castle.

266
00:28:05.190 --> 00:28:07.810
I want my daughters to be raised in their homeland

267
00:28:07.900 --> 00:28:11.480
with their family according to their birthright.

268
00:28:14.150 --> 00:28:16.950
And at my end. I want to die a dragonrider's death.

269
00:28:17.620 --> 00:28:19.910
Not that of some fat country lord.

270
00:28:53.650 --> 00:28:56.530
Soften your knees. Feet light.

271
00:28:58.110 --> 00:28:59.570
Keep your feet light and your hands heavy.

272
00:28:59.660 --> 00:29:02.200
This is the stuff. Lyonel.

273
00:29:02.290 --> 00:29:05.710
Lads that learn together. train together...

274
00:29:05.790 --> 00:29:08.000
knock each other down. pick each other up.

275
00:29:08.750 --> 00:29:11.540
They will certainly form a lifelong bond. Wouldn't you agree?

276
00:29:12.250 --> 00:29:13.670
That is the hope. Your Grace.

277
00:29:16.590 --> 00:29:19.220
Don't stand too upright. my Prince. You'll get knocked down.

278
00:29:30.350 --> 00:29:31.400
Aegon.

279
00:29:33.190 --> 00:29:37.360
I've won my first bout. Ser Criston. My opponent sues for mercy.

280
00:29:37.950 --> 00:29:40.320
You'll have a new opponent then. my Lord of the Straw.

281
00:29:41.280 --> 00:29:42.700
Let's see if you can touch me.

282
00:29:43.700 --> 00:29:44.950
You and your brother.

283
00:30:12.480 --> 00:30:14.270
You're going to have to do better than that.

284
00:30:19.990 --> 00:30:22.950
Weapons up. boys. Give your enemies no quarter.

285
00:30:25.790 --> 00:30:30.160
It seems the younger boys could do better with a bit of your attention. Ser Criston.

286
00:30:30.710 --> 00:30:33.040
You question my method of instruction. ser?

287
00:30:33.750 --> 00:30:37.170
Oh. I merely suggest that method be applied to all your pupils.

288
00:30:40.880 --> 00:30:41.930
Very well.

289
00:30:45.510 --> 00:30:48.810
Jacaerys. come here. You spar with Aegon.

290
00:30:51.850 --> 00:30:53.440
Eldest son against eldest son.

291
00:30:56.650 --> 00:30:59.190
It's hardly a fair match. I know you've never seen true battle. ser

292
00:30:59.280 --> 00:31:02.280
but when steel is drawn. a fair match isn't something anyone should expect.

293
00:31:04.780 --> 00:31:05.830
Blades up.

294
00:31:07.540 --> 00:31:08.790
Engage.

295
00:31:32.940 --> 00:31:34.480
- Foul play. - I'll deal with him.

296
00:31:37.770 --> 00:31:40.070
Plant your feet. You have a height advantage.

297
00:31:40.150 --> 00:31:42.280
Use it. Advance on him...

298
00:31:46.700 --> 00:31:47.830
You

299
00:31:49.290 --> 00:31:50.410
Close with him.

300
00:31:51.370 --> 00:31:53.540
Press him backward  Close with him

301
00:31:54.080 --> 00:31:56.040
Stay on the attack  Use your feet

302
00:31:59.630 --> 00:32:00.960
Don't let him get up.

303
00:32:02.970 --> 00:32:04.220
Stay on the attack

304
00:32:05.590 --> 00:32:06.760
Enough

305
00:32:08.550 --> 00:32:11.100
- You dare put hands on me? - Aegon

306
00:32:11.270 --> 00:32:13.230
You forget yourself. Strong. That is the Prince.

307
00:32:13.310 --> 00:32:14.770
This is what you teach. Cole?

308
00:32:17.400 --> 00:32:20.690
Cruelty... to the weaker opponent?

309
00:32:23.820 --> 00:32:27.030
Your interest in the princeling's training is quite unusual. Commander.

310
00:32:29.240 --> 00:32:32.250
Most men would only have that kind of devotion toward a cousin...

311
00:32:34.370 --> 00:32:35.410
or a brother...

312
00:32:36.620 --> 00:32:37.750
or a son.

313
00:32:54.680 --> 00:32:55.730
Get back

314
00:32:56.350 --> 00:32:57.690
Say it again

315
00:32:58.650 --> 00:32:59.940
Say it again

316
00:33:00.860 --> 00:33:01.940
Thought as much.

317
00:33:05.360 --> 00:33:06.860
Let him be bathed with a cloth

318
00:33:06.950 --> 00:33:10.450
and see to it the cook gives you a good. clear wine to drink.

319
00:33:13.080 --> 00:33:14.160
Princess...

320
00:33:14.870 --> 00:33:17.870
there's been an incident in the yard.

321
00:33:27.720 --> 00:33:29.840
It fills me with unrelenting shame.

322
00:33:29.930 --> 00:33:33.140
So that's what this is about then?

323
00:33:33.220 --> 00:33:34.770
- Your shame. - Our shame. Harwin

324
00:33:35.980 --> 00:33:37.520
Shame on the whole of House Strong.

325
00:33:37.600 --> 00:33:40.350
Because I laid my hands on that insufferable Cole...

326
00:33:40.440 --> 00:33:42.730
the son of a steward? He is a knight of the Kingsguard now.

327
00:33:42.820 --> 00:33:45.070
- He assailed Prince Jacaerys... - A defender of the crown

328
00:33:45.150 --> 00:33:46.740
the future heir to the throne.

329
00:33:48.860 --> 00:33:51.280
You have laid us open

330
00:33:51.370 --> 00:33:54.580
to accusations of an uglier treachery.

331
00:33:54.660 --> 00:33:56.700
And what treachery is that?

332
00:33:59.540 --> 00:34:01.540
Don't play the fool with me. boy.

333
00:34:03.380 --> 00:34:07.210
Your intimacy with the Princess Rhaenyra

334
00:34:07.300 --> 00:34:09.510
is an offense that would mean exile and death

335
00:34:10.130 --> 00:34:13.600
for you. for her. for the children

336
00:34:14.760 --> 00:34:16.850
It is rumor only...

337
00:34:19.020 --> 00:34:22.270
spun by the Princess's rivals. People have eyes. boy.

338
00:34:24.980 --> 00:34:28.650
Yet His Grace the King. it seems. will not accept what his eyes see.

339
00:34:29.450 --> 00:34:33.950
This flimsy shield alone stands between you and the headsman.

340
00:34:35.120 --> 00:34:37.750
The willful blindness of a father towards his child.

341
00:34:38.330 --> 00:34:40.710
I wish my father affected a similar blindness.

342
00:34:40.790 --> 00:34:43.040
Have I not these many years?

343
00:34:43.670 --> 00:34:44.920
And yet today.

344
00:34:45.000 --> 00:34:48.420
you publicly assaulted a knight of the Kingsguard in the... in the defense of your...

345
00:34:51.760 --> 00:34:54.640
You have your honor and I have mine.

346
00:35:03.150 --> 00:35:04.560
To ease the pain. Princess.

347
00:35:17.450 --> 00:35:20.200
- Thank you. - You'll feel better in a day or two

348
00:35:20.290 --> 00:35:21.460
when the milk dries up.

349
00:35:40.390 --> 00:35:41.680
My dear wife.

350
00:35:42.690 --> 00:35:43.730
Princess.

351
00:35:46.310 --> 00:35:47.480
I fell down.

352
00:35:49.730 --> 00:35:52.780
- Where have you been? - Out with Qarl. Didn't I mention it?

353
00:35:54.910 --> 00:35:56.320
Are you in very much pain?

354
00:35:57.240 --> 00:35:58.280
The milk...

355
00:35:59.410 --> 00:36:00.490
- swells the breasts... - Would you mind. Ser Qarl?

356
00:36:00.580 --> 00:36:03.370
I would like to speak with my husband.

357
00:36:03.540 --> 00:36:04.830
Of course. Princess.

358
00:36:16.680 --> 00:36:20.310
War is afoot again in the Stepstones. Rhaenyra.

359
00:36:21.720 --> 00:36:25.810
The Triarchy takes new life from its alliance with Dorne.

360
00:36:27.150 --> 00:36:28.900
They're waylaying ships and cargo.

361
00:36:29.820 --> 00:36:32.530
Qarl's been fighting there. He showed me a...

362
00:36:35.700 --> 00:36:39.580
He showed me a sack of sapphires big as walnuts

363
00:36:39.660 --> 00:36:41.450
that he took from a pirate he slew.

364
00:36:44.160 --> 00:36:47.580
After all this time. this is just what I need.

365
00:36:47.670 --> 00:36:49.340
A little adventure.

366
00:36:49.420 --> 00:36:52.380
A good. honest battle to enliven my blood again.

367
00:36:53.960 --> 00:36:57.800
He says there is a Tyroshi general there. A giant. they say...

368
00:36:58.470 --> 00:37:02.970
who dyes his beard purple and wears women's frocks.

369
00:37:06.690 --> 00:37:08.400
A few months. maybe...

370
00:37:13.650 --> 00:37:15.570
To be back at sea.

371
00:37:17.490 --> 00:37:18.740
Are you mad?

372
00:37:20.320 --> 00:37:21.830
Do you know what's happened

373
00:37:23.080 --> 00:37:26.790
while you've been guzzling all the ale in Flea Bottom? Gods know what besides?

374
00:37:27.870 --> 00:37:31.790
Dark rumors are hunting us. Laenor. They nip at our heels.

375
00:37:32.340 --> 00:37:33.590
Questions

376
00:37:34.670 --> 00:37:37.260
about our sons' parentage.

377
00:37:38.220 --> 00:37:40.720
Vile. disgusting insinuations.

378
00:37:41.640 --> 00:37:43.140
Insinuations. are they?

379
00:37:43.720 --> 00:37:45.680
They are our sons

380
00:37:45.770 --> 00:37:47.560
Yours and mine.

381
00:37:48.640 --> 00:37:50.770
And their true father will not abandon them now

382
00:37:50.850 --> 00:37:53.360
to go carousing through the Narrow Sea

383
00:37:53.440 --> 00:37:55.400
waggling his sword and winking at his sailors.

384
00:37:55.480 --> 00:37:56.780
I am a knight.

385
00:37:59.070 --> 00:38:01.320
And a warrior.

386
00:38:01.410 --> 00:38:06.290
And I have played my part here. faithfully...

387
00:38:07.710 --> 00:38:10.420
for ten years.

388
00:38:11.830 --> 00:38:14.590
- I am owed some... - You are owed nothing

389
00:38:15.840 --> 00:38:20.010
For ten years you have indulged yourself at court

390
00:38:20.880 --> 00:38:23.300
bought the finest horses

391
00:38:23.600 --> 00:38:27.520
drunk the rarest of wines fucked the lustiest boys.

392
00:38:27.600 --> 00:38:30.730
This was our agreement. I have not begrudged you.

393
00:38:31.900 --> 00:38:32.940
But...

394
00:38:34.770 --> 00:38:38.150
you do not desert your post when the storm lashes.

395
00:38:39.030 --> 00:38:43.280
The wise sailor flees the storm as it gathers.

396
00:38:54.040 --> 00:38:56.250
Very well then. I command you.

397
00:38:57.760 --> 00:38:59.970
As your Princess and the heir to the throne

398
00:39:00.050 --> 00:39:04.930
you are commanded to remain in King's Landing and at my side.

399
00:39:25.910 --> 00:39:27.660
It's been eight years. sweetling.

400
00:39:29.160 --> 00:39:32.330
- Half of them never do. you know? - What?

401
00:39:35.250 --> 00:39:36.290
Hatch.

402
00:39:39.300 --> 00:39:40.670
Will they let me stay?

403
00:39:42.340 --> 00:39:43.720
Will who let you stay?

404
00:39:44.550 --> 00:39:45.890
The Prince of Pentos.

405
00:39:47.180 --> 00:39:48.430
I don't understand.

406
00:39:50.020 --> 00:39:51.810
He wants you and father...

407
00:39:53.310 --> 00:39:54.560
and Baela...

408
00:39:55.270 --> 00:39:56.770
because you have dragons.

409
00:40:01.610 --> 00:40:05.320
There is more than one way to bind yourself to a dragon.

410
00:40:05.660 --> 00:40:09.370
I was without one until I was 15 years old

411
00:40:10.080 --> 00:40:14.160
and now I ride Vhagar. the largest in the world.

412
00:40:17.710 --> 00:40:21.130
You have a harder road. Baela's dragon was born to her.

413
00:40:24.050 --> 00:40:28.350
But if you wish to be a rider. you must claim that right.

414
00:40:30.310 --> 00:40:32.180
Your father would tell you the same.

415
00:40:33.890 --> 00:40:35.230
Father ignores me.

416
00:40:42.230 --> 00:40:43.650
He's doing his best.

417
00:41:21.860 --> 00:41:23.400
Laenor has written.

418
00:41:25.320 --> 00:41:27.400
Rhaenyra has delivered another son.

419
00:41:29.870 --> 00:41:31.450
Does your brother mention

420
00:41:31.530 --> 00:41:34.580
if this one also bears a marked but entirely coincidental resemblance

421
00:41:34.660 --> 00:41:36.370
to the Commander of the City Watch?

422
00:41:37.920 --> 00:41:40.380
He seems to have left that detail out.

423
00:41:43.340 --> 00:41:45.170
I miss my brother. Daemon.

424
00:41:47.880 --> 00:41:49.090
As I think do you.

425
00:41:51.180 --> 00:41:53.350
I miss Westerosi strongwine.

426
00:41:55.100 --> 00:41:57.850
It could be depended on for a few hours of peaceful oblivion.

427
00:41:59.940 --> 00:42:02.020
This amber shit that they drink here.

428
00:42:10.160 --> 00:42:11.530
Do you never long for home?

429
00:42:12.280 --> 00:42:13.330
No.

430
00:42:13.990 --> 00:42:16.290
- I don't believe you. - Believe what you please.

431
00:42:16.370 --> 00:42:20.580
You laud the virtues of Pentos. but you have no interest in it.

432
00:42:20.670 --> 00:42:22.630
If you did. you would venture into the city

433
00:42:22.710 --> 00:42:25.670
but instead. you spend your time here. in the library

434
00:42:25.750 --> 00:42:28.550
reading accounts of the same dead dragonlords

435
00:42:28.630 --> 00:42:31.640
whose legacy you claim has no hold on you.

436
00:42:31.720 --> 00:42:34.390
Didn't know I was being so minutely observed.

437
00:42:34.470 --> 00:42:35.680
You do not sleep.

438
00:42:35.760 --> 00:42:38.230
Well. how can I with you haunting my every move?

439
00:42:41.770 --> 00:42:43.940
Life has. I know. disappointed you.

440
00:42:45.270 --> 00:42:47.780
Perhaps I. too. am not the wife you would've wished for yourself.

441
00:42:47.860 --> 00:42:49.070
Laena.

442
00:42:49.440 --> 00:42:50.740
It does not pain me.

443
00:42:51.910 --> 00:42:53.490
I have made my peace.

444
00:42:57.790 --> 00:42:59.370
But you are more than this. Daemon.

445
00:43:01.920 --> 00:43:04.590
The man I married was more than this.

446
00:43:12.630 --> 00:43:15.010
It is Lord Blackwood's contention. therefore

447
00:43:15.100 --> 00:43:17.850
that the Brackens moved the boundary stones in the dead of the night

448
00:43:17.930 --> 00:43:20.600
and put their horses to graze in his field.

449
00:43:20.680 --> 00:43:23.230
Why was this issue not brought before Lord Grover?

450
00:43:23.310 --> 00:43:26.440
Has he grown so feeble he cannot settle a quarrel over rocks?

451
00:43:26.520 --> 00:43:30.780
I've heard tale that Lord Grover's son now rules Riverrun in all but name.

452
00:43:30.860 --> 00:43:34.410
Well. he is also a Tully and this remains a Tully problem.

453
00:43:35.370 --> 00:43:36.490
I would agree.

454
00:43:37.530 --> 00:43:38.990
- If we may move on. my lords...

455
00:43:39.080 --> 00:43:41.500
- And yet the Brackens and the Blackwoods

456
00:43:41.580 --> 00:43:44.370
will use any excuse to spill each other's blood.

457
00:43:46.960 --> 00:43:50.090
So this dispute bears looking into.

458
00:43:50.170 --> 00:43:53.630
There will be countryfolk who know where the lines have been drawn for generations.

459
00:43:54.260 --> 00:43:55.510
That is easy enough.

460
00:43:56.600 --> 00:43:57.680
Of course.

461
00:44:00.520 --> 00:44:01.560
Ser Tyland.

462
00:44:04.020 --> 00:44:08.020
We should address the latest developments in the Stepstones. my lords.

463
00:44:08.110 --> 00:44:10.530
Will we ever be shut of that blasted place?

464
00:44:10.610 --> 00:44:14.280
If you ask me. I think the Blackwoods have the upper hand. - No.

465
00:44:14.360 --> 00:44:16.820
We've moved on to the Stepstones. Lord Beesbury.

466
00:44:16.910 --> 00:44:19.990
And the Triarchy's new alliance with Dorne.

467
00:44:20.080 --> 00:44:22.660
I was hoping our negotiations with Sunspear

468
00:44:22.750 --> 00:44:24.750
might persuade them to see reason.

469
00:44:26.380 --> 00:44:29.000
To trust a Martell is to be disappointed.

470
00:44:29.090 --> 00:44:31.590
And where. I wonder. is our Prince Daemon?

471
00:44:31.670 --> 00:44:33.090
Or I suppose I should call him King

472
00:44:33.170 --> 00:44:35.510
as he styled himself when he won a battle there. once.

473
00:44:35.590 --> 00:44:36.720
That was a decade ago

474
00:44:36.800 --> 00:44:39.600
and he has since left the region undefended.

475
00:44:39.680 --> 00:44:41.520
We have left it undefended.

476
00:44:41.600 --> 00:44:45.270
There should've been fortifications built.

477
00:44:45.350 --> 00:44:49.150
Watchtowers. a fleet of ships... a garrison of soldiers sent to hold our ground.

478
00:44:49.230 --> 00:44:50.440
We cannot afford it.

479
00:44:52.780 --> 00:44:55.650
Our coffers are great but not infinite.

480
00:44:56.860 --> 00:44:58.820
We must consider the cost to our subjects.

481
00:44:58.910 --> 00:45:01.700
- I must agree. - The cost of war is greater.

482
00:45:04.290 --> 00:45:08.170
But we have been lax and the old monster now lifts its head.

483
00:45:13.710 --> 00:45:14.880
Let us be finished.

484
00:45:15.220 --> 00:45:17.630
Yes.

485
00:45:21.890 --> 00:45:22.930
Wait.

486
00:45:23.930 --> 00:45:25.060
I wish to speak.

487
00:45:26.770 --> 00:45:27.810
Be seated.

488
00:45:37.280 --> 00:45:39.990
I have felt the...

489
00:45:41.490 --> 00:45:42.530
strife...

490
00:45:43.700 --> 00:45:46.040
between our families of late. my Queen.

491
00:45:48.750 --> 00:45:52.170
And for any offense given by mine. I apologize.

492
00:45:54.670 --> 00:45:56.380
But we are one house.

493
00:45:57.840 --> 00:46:01.340
And long before that. we were friends.

494
00:46:08.060 --> 00:46:10.900
My son Jacaerys will inherit the Iron Throne after me.

495
00:46:10.980 --> 00:46:13.570
I propose we betroth him to your daughter. Helaena.

496
00:46:15.440 --> 00:46:18.950
Ally ourselves... once and for all.

497
00:46:20.530 --> 00:46:24.280
Let them rule together. A most judicious proposition.

498
00:46:29.330 --> 00:46:33.040
Additionally. if Syrax brings forth another clutch of eggs

499
00:46:33.130 --> 00:46:35.460
your son Aemond will have his choice of them.

500
00:46:36.710 --> 00:46:39.050
A symbol of our goodwill.

501
00:46:42.300 --> 00:46:43.350
Rhaenyra.

502
00:46:52.190 --> 00:46:53.230
Oh. Seven Hells.

503
00:46:56.320 --> 00:47:00.530
My dear. A dragon's egg is a handsome gift.

504
00:47:01.990 --> 00:47:05.700
The King and I thank you for your offer and we will consider it duly.

505
00:47:05.780 --> 00:47:07.410
You must rest now. husband.

506
00:47:10.960 --> 00:47:12.000
Yes.

507
00:47:18.760 --> 00:47:22.430
How sweetly the fox speaks when it's being cornered by the hounds.

508
00:47:22.510 --> 00:47:23.800
- She is sincere.

509
00:47:24.390 --> 00:47:25.800
- She is desperate.

510
00:47:25.890 --> 00:47:28.060
She feels the earth washing away beneath her feet

511
00:47:28.140 --> 00:47:30.640
and now she expects us to ignore her transgressions

512
00:47:30.730 --> 00:47:33.810
and for me to marry my only daughter to one of her...

513
00:47:33.900 --> 00:47:35.110
plain-featured sons.

514
00:47:35.650 --> 00:47:37.900
The proposal is a good one. my Queen.

515
00:47:39.360 --> 00:47:40.900
We're a family.

516
00:47:40.990 --> 00:47:45.450
Let us put aside these childish quarrels. Join hands and be stronger for it.

517
00:47:46.950 --> 00:47:48.740
You may do as you wish. husband...

518
00:47:50.040 --> 00:47:52.040
when I am cold in my grave.

519
00:47:53.210 --> 00:47:54.250
Alicent.

520
00:47:56.210 --> 00:47:57.250
Alicent

521
00:48:20.900 --> 00:48:22.440
I do not need the blanket...

522
00:48:26.410 --> 00:48:27.570
The Hand. Your Grace.

523
00:48:28.580 --> 00:48:31.040
- The King is resting. - I will see him.

524
00:48:32.750 --> 00:48:33.870
Lean forward.

525
00:48:41.420 --> 00:48:44.340
I'm being endlessly fussed over. Lyonel.

526
00:48:45.050 --> 00:48:47.430
It's a wonder I can visit the privy alone.

527
00:48:48.350 --> 00:48:49.390
Your Grace.

528
00:48:50.510 --> 00:48:52.600
What might this errand be about. Lord Lyonel?

529
00:48:55.560 --> 00:48:56.810
Your Grace. I feel...

530
00:48:59.480 --> 00:49:02.030
I have come to resign my position as Hand of the King.

531
00:49:03.610 --> 00:49:05.490
The episode in the yard this morning.

532
00:49:05.570 --> 00:49:08.490
My son Harwin has disgraced himself

533
00:49:08.570 --> 00:49:11.490
and every fishwife in King's Landing will soon be telling the tale.

534
00:49:11.580 --> 00:49:15.040
Young Harwin's outburst was unfortunate. it's true

535
00:49:15.830 --> 00:49:17.500
but he's been expelled from the City Watch.

536
00:49:17.580 --> 00:49:21.090
That seems punishment enough. Forgive me. Your Grace. it is not.

537
00:49:28.640 --> 00:49:34.100
You have served me faithfully for many years... ten as Hand.

538
00:49:35.680 --> 00:49:39.600
Your advice has been sage. unmarked by self-interest

539
00:49:40.560 --> 00:49:43.360
which stands in contrast to all others.

540
00:49:44.780 --> 00:49:46.190
You speak kind words

541
00:49:47.530 --> 00:49:51.700
but there is a shadow over my house and it grows ever darker.

542
00:49:51.780 --> 00:49:54.330
I can no longer serve you with integrity.

543
00:49:55.830 --> 00:49:57.040
What is this shadow?

544
00:49:58.830 --> 00:50:00.790
Name it. if it casts such a gloom.

545
00:50:01.380 --> 00:50:05.670
Yes. we must have your reasoning in plain language.

546
00:50:13.810 --> 00:50:14.850
I cannot.

547
00:50:17.180 --> 00:50:19.690
Then I cannot accept this. - My dear husband...

548
00:50:19.770 --> 00:50:20.810
- I said no.

549
00:50:22.110 --> 00:50:24.270
- If you insist. my King. - I do.

550
00:50:25.690 --> 00:50:27.690
You will continue in your service to the crown.

551
00:50:30.410 --> 00:50:32.450
I would then ask leave to take my son from court

552
00:50:32.530 --> 00:50:34.990
and escort him back to the family seat at Harrenhal.

553
00:50:35.700 --> 00:50:36.910
He is my heir

554
00:50:37.750 --> 00:50:39.660
and will be lord of Harren's castle one day.

555
00:50:39.750 --> 00:50:41.750
It is time he assumed his duties there.

556
00:50:45.250 --> 00:50:46.300
Do it.

557
00:51:07.110 --> 00:51:08.690
Aren't you gonna help me?

558
00:51:48.900 --> 00:51:51.610
I took the liberty of beginning without you. Your Grace.

559
00:51:51.690 --> 00:51:54.280
It seemed a sin to let such a pie grow cold.

560
00:51:54.450 --> 00:51:56.490
You did wisely. Lord Larys.

561
00:51:57.530 --> 00:52:00.040
Though you had no such worry about the wine. surely.

562
00:52:00.120 --> 00:52:02.960
Meat without wine is also a sin.

563
00:52:08.590 --> 00:52:11.210
It's been my duty to tell you of happenings about the castle

564
00:52:11.300 --> 00:52:14.130
but tonight you know and I do not.

565
00:52:15.090 --> 00:52:17.930
The King had an audience with my father.

566
00:52:18.010 --> 00:52:19.600
He attempted to resign his post.

567
00:52:20.640 --> 00:52:21.720
I thought as much.

568
00:52:23.350 --> 00:52:26.690
His honor's always been a millstone about his esteemed neck.

569
00:52:29.020 --> 00:52:30.980
Interesting. you said "attempted"?

570
00:52:31.070 --> 00:52:32.900
My lord husband refused to accept.

571
00:52:34.530 --> 00:52:38.280
Then he fell short of confessing my brother's transgressions.

572
00:52:38.370 --> 00:52:39.740
With his eruption in the yard

573
00:52:39.830 --> 00:52:42.250
your brother all but confessed the truth himself.

574
00:52:42.950 --> 00:52:45.040
Truth has many flavors. Your Grace.

575
00:52:46.250 --> 00:52:50.250
Do you expect the King to doom his dear daughter to exile or even...

576
00:52:52.300 --> 00:52:53.340
Talya. not now.

577
00:53:00.890 --> 00:53:02.390
It's a willful blindness. the King.

578
00:53:03.060 --> 00:53:06.600
I mean. you'd surely suffer the same affliction if it came to it.

579
00:53:06.690 --> 00:53:07.850
- I would not.

580
00:53:10.060 --> 00:53:12.940
Lord Lyonel is to escort Ser Harwin back to Harrenhal

581
00:53:13.030 --> 00:53:15.990
to watch over his seat whilst he continues to serve as Hand.

582
00:53:16.990 --> 00:53:21.280
But the Hand is compromised by the acts of his son.

583
00:53:21.780 --> 00:53:26.160
My father cannot give unbiased counsel to the King.

584
00:53:26.870 --> 00:53:29.750
It is now that I most rue the absence of my own father.

585
00:53:30.210 --> 00:53:32.300
He wouldn't hesitate to speak the truth to the King.

586
00:53:32.380 --> 00:53:35.010
If Otto Hightower were still Hand... You cannot say. my Queen

587
00:53:35.090 --> 00:53:37.930
that your father would be impartial in this matter.

588
00:53:38.010 --> 00:53:39.760
No. but he would be partial to me

589
00:53:49.600 --> 00:53:52.270
In all of King's Landing. is there no one to take my side?

590
00:54:18.630 --> 00:54:21.510
What a collection of heroes I have before me.

591
00:54:25.890 --> 00:54:27.020
A murderer...

592
00:54:28.020 --> 00:54:29.520
a deviant...

593
00:54:30.850 --> 00:54:32.310
a traitor to the crown.

594
00:54:33.520 --> 00:54:37.780
For your crimes. you've been sentenced to death by hanging.

595
00:54:39.820 --> 00:54:41.070
What do you want with us?

596
00:54:44.870 --> 00:54:47.750
I am prepared to offer you mercy

597
00:54:49.460 --> 00:54:52.380
if you're prepared to pay a little price.

598
00:55:17.150 --> 00:55:18.990
Push. my lady. Push

599
00:55:20.150 --> 00:55:22.950
Push  Push

600
00:55:23.030 --> 00:55:25.070
- You must push  - Push

601
00:55:27.490 --> 00:55:28.870
It needs to come now

602
00:55:29.870 --> 00:55:31.000
Push

603
00:55:33.170 --> 00:55:34.420
Push

604
00:55:35.590 --> 00:55:37.500
You must push now. my lady

605
00:55:38.760 --> 00:55:40.010
Push

606
00:55:58.480 --> 00:56:00.280
I've reached the limit of my art.

607
00:56:02.450 --> 00:56:03.910
The child will not come.

608
00:56:06.780 --> 00:56:08.280
My brave girl.

609
00:56:14.370 --> 00:56:15.580
I'm very sorry. my Prince.

610
00:56:17.590 --> 00:56:19.420
We could lay open the womb...

611
00:56:20.590 --> 00:56:23.840
try to remove the infant by way of the blade

612
00:56:25.760 --> 00:56:28.300
but I cannot say for a surety whether it lives.

613
00:56:28.890 --> 00:56:30.310
Would the mother survive it?

614
00:56:32.390 --> 00:56:33.430
No.

615
00:57:04.670 --> 00:57:05.720
Vhagar.

616
00:57:05.840 --> 00:57:07.470
dracarys.

617
00:57:12.270 --> 00:57:13.980
Dracarys

618
00:57:16.350 --> 00:57:18.310
Dracarys

619
00:57:22.150 --> 00:57:23.740
Dracarys...

620
00:57:24.440 --> 00:57:26.610
Dracarys

621
00:57:28.570 --> 00:57:29.950
Dracarys.

622
00:57:50.760 --> 00:57:51.800
Laena

623
00:58:14.910 --> 00:58:18.370
Be good to your mother. lads. I'll visit when I can.

624
00:58:22.130 --> 00:58:23.750
But that may be some time.

625
00:58:27.510 --> 00:58:28.550
Jace.

626
00:58:35.600 --> 00:58:36.640
I will return...

627
00:58:39.640 --> 00:58:40.770
I promise.

628
00:58:55.910 --> 00:58:59.580
I will be a stranger when we meet again.

629
00:59:16.810 --> 00:59:17.850
Princess.

630
00:59:40.250 --> 00:59:43.790
We will exchange letters by raven.

631
00:59:44.210 --> 00:59:46.040
- Won't that be fun? - Is Harwin Strong my father?

632
00:59:50.800 --> 00:59:52.220
Am I a bastard?

633
00:59:56.800 --> 00:59:58.180
You are a Targaryen.

634
01:00:00.640 --> 01:00:01.770
That's all that matters.

635
01:00:26.710 --> 01:00:27.750
A word?

636
01:00:34.760 --> 01:00:36.140
I take it he's gone.

637
01:00:38.600 --> 01:00:40.600
We're finished here. We're leaving.

638
01:00:43.480 --> 01:00:46.310
What of your offer? Jace and Helaena?

639
01:00:46.400 --> 01:00:48.110
I have been undermined and made a spectacle.

640
01:00:48.940 --> 01:00:52.280
They whisper about me in the corridors.

641
01:00:52.360 --> 01:00:54.650
Well. I leave them to it.

642
01:00:58.620 --> 01:00:59.870
To Dragonstone then?

643
01:01:00.700 --> 01:01:02.160
We should've left years ago.

644
01:01:08.170 --> 01:01:09.500
What of your position?

645
01:01:10.290 --> 01:01:12.550
You've always said if you were absent from court

646
01:01:12.630 --> 01:01:15.300
she would pour her honey in your father's ear.

647
01:01:16.220 --> 01:01:19.350
The wise sailor flees the storm as it gathers.

648
01:01:21.640 --> 01:01:22.680
Laenor...

649
01:01:24.850 --> 01:01:26.060
bring him.

650
01:01:27.850 --> 01:01:29.480
We'll need every sword we can muster.

651
01:02:47.390 --> 01:02:49.730
Fire  I will burn

652
01:02:49.810 --> 01:02:50.850
Harwin

653
01:02:51.730 --> 01:02:52.770
Harwin

654
01:03:17.090 --> 01:03:20.840
What are children but a weakness?

655
01:03:24.390 --> 01:03:25.510
A folly?

656
01:03:27.060 --> 01:03:28.560
A futility?

657
01:03:34.310 --> 01:03:38.860
Through them. you imagine you cheat the great darkness of its victory.

658
01:03:54.750 --> 01:03:59.760
You will persist forever in some form or another...

659
01:04:02.550 --> 01:04:05.140
as if they will keep you from the dust.

660
01:04:16.810 --> 01:04:20.990
But for them. you surrender what you should not.

661
01:04:24.240 --> 01:04:28.030
You may know what is the right thing to be done

662
01:04:28.120 --> 01:04:32.120
but love stays the hand.

663
01:04:40.460 --> 01:04:41.590
Love...

664
01:04:43.840 --> 01:04:45.470
is a downfall.

665
01:04:50.720 --> 01:04:54.190
Best to make your way through life unencumbered

666
01:04:55.980 --> 01:04:57.400
if you ask me.

667
01:05:00.940 --> 01:05:02.400
They're dead.

668
01:05:02.480 --> 01:05:05.030
You've heard the stories of Harrenhal. Your Grace.

669
01:05:07.070 --> 01:05:11.540
It was built in hubris by Harren the Black as a monument to his own greatness.

670
01:05:11.620 --> 01:05:14.290
Blood mixed into the mortar.

671
01:05:16.920 --> 01:05:19.290
It is said to be a cursed place.

672
01:05:20.000 --> 01:05:23.510
That it passes judgment on all who pass beneath its gates.

673
01:05:23.800 --> 01:05:25.420
You...

674
01:05:25.510 --> 01:05:27.090
You passed judgment.

675
01:05:29.140 --> 01:05:30.550
The Queen makes a wish.

676
01:05:32.350 --> 01:05:35.680
What servant of the realm would not strive to fulfill it?

677
01:05:38.100 --> 01:05:41.440
I assume you will write to your father now?

678
01:05:43.650 --> 01:05:44.740
Larys...

679
01:05:45.820 --> 01:05:48.070
I did not wish for this.

680
01:05:50.320 --> 01:05:53.330
I feel certain you will reward me...

681
01:05:55.910 --> 01:05:57.500
when the time is right.

681
